ai-patthana17.20:0.2_0: Having given the immaterial states produced by the phenomena that are counterpart of
ai-patthana17.20:0.3_0: Seeing their vows, doing good deeds,
ai-patthana17.20:1.1_0: It is the condition for the untroubledishment, not for the sake of non-existence, not for the sake of any offense of the Dhamma, and for the purpose of being condition.
ai-patthana17.20:2.1_0: There is a place for three objects, for the sake of which there is non-disappearance, when that which is exists in the sixth.
ai-patthana17.20:3.1_0: Not invisible, not undeclared, skillful teaching gives rise to repulsion.
ai-patthana17.20:3.1_1: Not invisible, not unprofitable states, orrofitable principles gives rise to repulsion.
ai-patthana17.20:3.1_2: Not invisible, skilled in questions of the Buddha, or skilled in loss, and skilled in means.
ai-patthana17.20:3.1_3: This is the section in brief.
ai-patthana17.20:5.1_0: Not for the skillful, no unskillful quality, no impingement arises in him.
ai-patthana17.20:5.1_1: Not for the skillful, no unskillful quality, no impingement arises in him.
ai-patthana17.20:5.1_2: A skillful person doesn’t give rise to unprofitableness, or skilled in dependent origination.
ai-patthana17.20:6.1_0: Unskillfulness doesn’t give rise to unskillful qualities.
ai-patthana17.20:6.1_1: Unskillfulness doesn’t give rise to unskillful qualities.
ai-patthana17.20:6.1_2: Unskillfulness doesn’t give rise to unskillfulness, and skilled in dependent origination. Thoughts don’t give rise to repulsion. Misconduct because of this. Their cause and unskillful qualities arise because of cause or reason.
ai-patthana17.20:7.1_0: Not invisible, not unprofitable principles, or dependently originated.
ai-patthana17.20:7.1_1: Not invisible, not unprofitable states, or dependently originated by what is unskillful.
ai-patthana17.20:7.1_2: Not unprofitable, not skilled in loss, and skilled in practicing the way. These don’t arise because of what is unskillful and what is unskillful.
ai-patthana17.20:8.1_0: A skillful teaching gives rise to repulsion, no indeterminate, and what is unskillful, no independent of others. ...
ai-patthana17.20:9.1_0: Unskillful, not unskillful, not skilled in loss, and what is unskillful. There is no cause or condition, no repulsion for what is unskillful, no value, repulsion, because of what is unskillful and no cause or condition.
ai-patthana17.20:9.1_1: This is the section in brief.
